text: I thought about putting gonti into glissa once I retool her. My article next week is over her and helping find some sort of identity. Let me know how gonti goes.
Go watch <@U3TH74LM6>'s gameplay video on Gonti. Its a fun build.
I have a new one out today. He's a blast to play.
Yup. I need to finish it up.
Your article is scheduled.
Your build is very 1v1 tuned, still lots  of fun
Awesome.
Yeah, all my builds are 1v1.
Some can be put into a multiplayer setting, others would be kind of soft.
Also man, I wish I could Impirial seal as often as you ddo
The biggest change to gonti in my mind to go multiplayer is blade of selves, get more triggers and happy times will be had
Oh, Cold Storage is another ‘blink’ artifact you can use with Gonti. It’s a little expensive, mana wise, but if you have Cabal Coffers, etc. that really isn’t a problem to get them triggers.
And let’s face it, allowing mono black to cast Villainous Wealth is worth everything...
I swear Gonti reads Dimir to me...
Hm, maybe some more pillow fort too for multiplayer, as you are going to make yourself a target, and you might need even more ramp if we are getting more triggers
Hahaha. Felt so good to fire that Villainous Wealth off.
Not really - you don’t have any time limit on when you cast the spells Gonti exiles
He doesn’t even need to be out.
You'd be getting more cards to play with though, but I'd have to see what I'd take out to get more in
The fact that he exiles face down prevents Pull from Eternity/Riftsweeper shennanigans too…what a card.
Eldrazi Processor’s can get them, but not your own stuff :wink:

If only Gonti was UB :(
Gonti is actually the reason I started brewing a copy-based Mimeoplasm deck briefly.
<@U3FV90TCZ> He reads Dimir, though, doesn’t he? I think that would make him too strong if he had access to blue (casting Sakashima the Impostor would be just too nuts with Gonti)
He probably would be honestly. Right now, with the limitations of MonoB he's interesting. If you added blue, he wouldn't be the same deck. He would just be a Deadeye+Palinchron Combo piece
He does read dimir, but that just means it is a black a blue identity
Yup…he is defined by his limiations.
limitations, that is.
Hrm…kinda makes me want to see how he’s do in an Athreos shell...
ignore the obvious ‘blueness’ all the more.

Just give him and Brago partner with each other and call it a day lol.
Athreos is interesting, but I've never been happy with his concept. I've never really had a deck that could play him though.
So he might play better than he reads
We could try to pull a josh lee Kwai and try to make a 5 color gonti

Melanie
melanie pulls all the strings

Any opinions on ethersworn adjudicator? Mines been in Breya since I bought it but I'm trying to streamline the deck but I haven't actually drawn it enough to form an opinion but it feels clunky
It IS clunky
I have no haste enablers either so it's literally a delayed way to kill an artifact or a creature for 8 mana, only plus side is the body is okay
It's nice with enablers like Unwinding clock, but otherwise it's really slow.
It is clunky, but on the other hand, Feldon of the third path with it in the yard is wonderful
Is it?
Explain yourself!
As long as nobody is clamoring for me to not cut it I'm gonna try skipping it for now
Cut it.
Copy, kill things, but my Breya deck is also way more about copying artifacts
But...you have to pay 3 and tap to reanimate it and then another 3 and tap to kill a thing. That seems even clunkier.
Yeah I want to be doing better things for six mana and tapping a creature.
I don't run Feldon either for the same reason haha
I mean it's not the worst option to have available but Feldon was cut early in favor of other reanimation stuff
Feldon is in my Breya pile, but he's not a shoo-in to stay.
Idk feldon can be cool with something more agressive like Wurmcoil but it's never a bomb
My only issue with Breya is that it's so hard to make cuts when you're in 4 colors plus artifacts...
